.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mra0xnbh/06ad581c-f068-4ba4-9bb3-41758f6fae55/bd09bfd0-79aa-11f1-9eb6-139adce7efb6/file-6y3zli1mra0xnbi.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mra0xnbh/06ad581c-f068-4ba4-9bb3-41758f6fae55/bd09bfd0-79aa-11f1-9eb6-139adce7efb6/file-6y3zli1mra0xnbi.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","question":"<p>The wedge is moved towards right with acceleration $a$ which is slowly increased from zero. Find tension in the string just when the small block breaks contact with the surface of the wedge. (Assume all surfaces are smooth and string is inextensible)</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mra0xnbh/06ad581c-f068-4ba4-9bb3-41758f6fae55/bd09bfd0-79aa-11f1-9eb6-139adce7efb6/file-6y3zli1mra0xnbi.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mra0xnbh/06ad581c-f068-4ba4-9bb3-41758f6fae55/bd09bfd0-79aa-11f1-9eb6-139adce7efb6/file-6y3zli1mra0xnbi.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","options":["<p>2mg sin θ</p>","<p>mg cosec θ</p>","<p>mg tan θ</p>","<p>mg cot θ</p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"ExamGoal JEE Main 2027","image":null,"_examgoalId":"tq-mra132o0","_bank":"examgoal_2027"},{"id":319022322,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>A block of mass <b>m</b> resting on a wedge of angle $\\theta$ as shown in the figure. The wedge is given an acceleration <b>a</b> towards left. What is the minimum value of <b>a</b> due to external agent so that the mass <b>m</b> falls freely?</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr3cohxz/e810c3f1-ffdc-458e-ae57-6532a31f4ca9/2f9b8e70-75ff-11f1-bfda-ab45182f57fb/file-6y3zli1mr3cohy0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https