b> and <b>n<sup>th</sup></b> blocks is</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr9xteyf/a62443c1-d2cc-458d-8002-7d0047ade656/8bf44070-799e-11f1-9eb6-139adce7efb6/file-6y3zli1mr9xteyg.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr9xteyf/a62443c1-d2cc-458d-8002-7d0047ade656/8bf44070-799e-11f1-9eb6-139adce7efb6/file-6y3zli1mr9xteyg.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","options":["<p><b>$(m_{n-1} - m_n) g \\sin\\theta$</b></p>","<p><b>zero</b></p>","<p><b>$m_{n-1} m_n g \\cos\\theta$</b></p>","<p><b>None of these</b></p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"ExamGoal JEE Main 2027","image":null,"_examgoalId":"tq-mr9y25dx","_bank":"examgoal_2027"},{"id":1651851407,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>A trolley is being pulled up an inclined plane by a man sitting on it (as shown in figure). He applies a force of 250 N. If the combined mass of the man and trolley is 100 kg, the acceleration of the trolley will be [Use, $\\sin 15^{\\circ} = 0.26$, $g = 10 \\rm{m/s^2}$]</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mra15ntb/f966e68c-4718-4a24-8608-f522e998b288/9be4d5f0-79ab-11f1-9eb6-139adce7efb6/file-6y3zli1mra15ntc.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mra15ntb/f966e68c-4718-4a24-8608-f522e998b288/9be4d5f0-79ab-11f1-9eb6-139adce7efb6/file-6y3zli1mra15ntc.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","question":"<p>A trolley is being pulled up an inclined plane by a man sitting on it (as shown in figure). He applies a force of 250 N. If the combined mass of the man and trolley is 100 kg, the acceleration of the trolley will be [Use, $\\sin 15^{\\circ} = 0.26$, $g = 10 \\rm{m/s^2}$]</p>\n<img 